# Introduction / はじめに
![bg right:40%](assets/images/new_year_background.jpg)

- Japanese New Year (お正月) is one of the most important holidays
- Traditional customs and celebrations
- Family gatherings and special foods
- Unique decorations and rituals

---

# Shishimai / 獅子舞
![center-image](assets/images/shishimai.png)

- Traditional lion dance performance
- Brings good luck and wards off evil spirits
- Often performed at shrines and temples
- Important part of New Year celebrations

---

# Kadomatsu / 門松
![center-image](assets/images/kadomatsu.png)

- Traditional decoration placed at entrances
- Made of bamboo, pine, and plum branches
- Welcomes ancestral spirits and deities
- Displayed from late December to January 7th

---

# Kagami Mochi / 鏡餅

<div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-around;">
